main event: A sighting of an unidentified object, potentially a craft, was reported in the Pacific Ocean on 29 August 1962.
interesting points: The object was observed for 4 minutes,The object's brightness and size were compared to Venus,The object's speed seemed irregular and maneuverability was limited,The object moved southwest and disappeared behind the horizon,No trails were observed from the object.
witness description: Luis Simpson, OCS Dane, SN, Lookout, Excellent
